*******************
**** OS Module ****
*******************
https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v12.x/docs/api/os.html

To load the module:
const OS = require('os');

There are some useful methods such as:
freemem() returns how much free memory is on the machine.
totalmem() returns memory total.
userinfo([options]) Info about the current user.
uptime() gets the uptime of the machine.

Quick example of using it:

const OS = require("os");
const totalMemory = OS.totalmem();
const freeMem = OS.freemem();
console.log(`Total Mem: ${totalMemory} Free Mem:${freeMem}`);
